        "abstract": "<jats:title>ABSTRACT</jats:title><jats:sec><jats:title/><jats:p>Many difficult-to-understand clinical features characterize COVID-19 and post-acute sequelae of COVID-19 (PASC or long COVID [LC]). The SARS-CoV-2 Spike protein receptor-binding domain (RBD) binds angiotensin converting enzyme 2 (ACE2) on the surface of host cells to initiate infection.</jats:p></jats:sec><jats:sec><jats:title>IMPORTANCE</jats:title><jats:p>Patients who have had COVID-19 can sometimes have troublesome symptoms, termed post-acute sequelae of COVID-19 (PASC) or long COVID (LC). We show that patients convalescing from COVID-19 also make antibodies that act like ACE2.</jats:p></jats:sec>",
